-{"id":"bd-267","title":"Unit tests for semantic color theme with color degradation","description":"## Purpose
Create comprehensive unit tests for the Theme module, ensuring semantic colors work correctly and color degradation functions properly across different terminal capabilities.

## Why This Matters
The theme system must:
1. Provide consistent semantic meaning (success=green, error=red)
2. Degrade gracefully across 24-bit, 8-bit, and 4-bit terminals
3. Never crash or output invalid codes

## Test Categories

### 1. Semantic Color Tests
```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod theme_tests {
    use super::*;

    #[test]
    fn test_success_color_is_green_family() {
        let theme = Theme::default();
        let color = theme.success();
        // In truecolor mode, should be some shade of green
        assert\!(is_green_ish(color));
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_error_color_is_red_family() {
        let theme = Theme::default();
        let color = theme.error();
        assert\!(is_red_ish(color));
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_warning_color_is_yellow_family() {
        let theme = Theme::default();
        let color = theme.warning();
        assert\!(is_yellow_ish(color));
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_primary_color_is_cyan_family() {
        let theme = Theme::default();
        let color = theme.primary();
        assert\!(is_cyan_ish(color));
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_muted_color_is_dim() {
        let theme = Theme::default();
        let style = theme.muted_style();
        assert\!(style.has_dim() || is_gray(style.foreground()));
    }
}
```

### 2. Color Degradation Tests
```rust
#[test]
fn test_truecolor_preserved_in_truecolor_terminal() {
    let theme = Theme::with_color_depth(ColorDepth::TrueColor);
    let color = theme.success();
    // Should be exact RGB value
    assert\!(matches\!(color, Color::Rgb(_, _, _)));
}

#[test]
fn test_truecolor_degrades_to_256() {
    let theme = Theme::with_color_depth(ColorDepth::EightBit);
    let color = theme.success();
    // Should be 256-color palette index
    assert\!(matches\!(color, Color::Index(_)));
}

#[test]
fn test_truecolor_degrades_to_16() {
    let theme = Theme::with_color_depth(ColorDepth::Basic);
    let color = theme.success();
    // Should be basic color name
    assert\!(matches\!(color, Color::Named(_)));
}

#[test]
fn test_no_color_returns_default() {
    let theme = Theme::with_color_depth(ColorDepth::None);
    let color = theme.success();
    assert_eq\!(color, Color::Default);
}

#[test]
fn test_color_degradation_maintains_intent() {
    // Success should always be recognizable as 'green' at any depth
    for depth in [ColorDepth::TrueColor, ColorDepth::EightBit, ColorDepth::Basic] {
        let theme = Theme::with_color_depth(depth);
        let color = theme.success();
        assert\!(is_green_family(color), "Success not green at {:?}", depth);
    }
}
```

### 3. Style Composition Tests
```rust
#[test]
fn test_success_style_has_foreground() {
    let theme = Theme::default();
    let style = theme.success_style();
    assert\!(style.foreground().is_some());
}

#[test]
fn test_error_style_is_bold() {
    let theme = Theme::default();
    let style = theme.error_style();
    assert\!(style.has_bold());
}

#[test]
fn test_heading_style_combines_attributes() {
    let theme = Theme::default();
    let style = theme.heading_style();
    assert\!(style.has_bold());
    assert\!(style.foreground().is_some());
}

#[test]
fn test_style_merge_preserves_both() {
    let theme = Theme::default();
    let base = theme.success_style();
    let merged = base.with_underline();
    assert\!(merged.has_underline());
    assert_eq\!(merged.foreground(), base.foreground());
}
```

### 4. Custom Theme Tests
```rust
#[test]
fn test_custom_theme_overrides_colors() {
    let theme = Theme::builder()
        .success(Color::Rgb(0, 200, 100))  // Different green
        .build();
    let color = theme.success();
    assert_eq\!(color, Color::Rgb(0, 200, 100));
}

#[test]
fn test_theme_clone_is_independent() {
    let theme1 = Theme::default();
    let theme2 = theme1.clone();
    // Modifying one shouldn't affect the other (if mutable)
}
```

### 5. ANSI Code Generation Tests
```rust
#[test]
fn test_style_to_ansi_has_reset() {
    let theme = Theme::default();
    let style = theme.success_style();
    let ansi = style.to_ansi_string("test");
    assert\!(ansi.ends_with("\x1b[0m") || ansi.contains("\x1b[0m"));
}

#[test]
fn test_nested_styles_reset_correctly() {
    let theme = Theme::default();
    let ansi = theme.render_markup("[bold][red]nested[/][/]");
    // Should have proper resets, not cumulative codes
}
```

## Test Helpers
```rust
fn is_green_ish(color: Color) -> bool {
    match color {
        Color::Rgb(r, g, b) => g > r && g > b,
        Color::Index(idx) => [2, 10, 28, 34, 40, 46, 82, 118, 154].contains(&idx),
        Color::Named(name) => name == "green" || name == "bright_green",
        _ => false,
    }
}
```

## Logging Requirements
```rust
#[test]
fn test_with_logging() {
    let _guard = init_test_logging();
    tracing::info\!("Testing color degradation");
    let theme = Theme::with_color_depth(ColorDepth::Basic);
    tracing::debug\!(depth = ?ColorDepth::Basic, color = ?theme.success(), "Degraded color");
}
```

## Files to Create
- src/output/theme.rs: Add #[cfg(test)] module
- tests/theme_tests.rs: Integration tests

## Success Criteria
- All semantic colors tested
- Color degradation verified at all depths
- Style composition works correctly
- ANSI output is valid
