 {"id":"bd-2ao","title":"Create data formatters (src/output/formatters.rs)","description":"# Create Data Formatters

## What
Create src/output/formatters.rs containing functions that format data values (bytes, durations, IPs, etc.) with consistent styling.

## Why
Data values appear throughout rust_proxy output (bytes transferred, ping latency, timestamps). Formatting them consistently with appropriate colors makes output scannable and professional.

## Formatters to Implement

### Byte Formatting
```rust
/// Format bytes with color (e.g., "1.2 GB" in magenta)
pub fn format_bytes_rich(bytes: u64) -> String {
    let formatted = crate::util::format_bytes(bytes);
    format!("[bright_magenta]{}[/]", formatted)
}
```

### Duration Formatting
```rust
/// Format duration with color (e.g., "2d 3h 45m" in cyan)
pub fn format_duration_rich(secs: u64) -> String {
    let formatted = crate::util::format_duration(secs);
    format!("[bright_cyan]{}[/]", formatted)
}
```

### Latency Formatting (with thresholds)
```rust
/// Format ping latency with color coding based on value:
/// - <100ms = green (good)
/// - <300ms = yellow (acceptable)
/// - >=300ms = red (slow)
/// - None = gray "--"
pub fn format_latency_rich(ms: Option<f64>) -> String {
    match ms {
        Some(ms) if ms < 100.0 => format!("[green]{:.0}ms[/]", ms),
        Some(ms) if ms < 300.0 => format!("[yellow]{:.0}ms[/]", ms),
        Some(ms) => format!("[red]{:.0}ms[/]", ms),
        None => "[bright_black]--[/]".to_string(),
    }
}
```

### IP Address Formatting
```rust
/// Format IP address (bright yellow for visibility)
pub fn format_ip_rich(ip: &str) -> String {
    format!("[bright_yellow]{}[/]", ip)
}
```

### Domain Formatting
```rust
/// Format domain name (bright blue)
pub fn format_domain_rich(domain: &str) -> String {
    format!("[bright_blue]{}[/]", domain)
}
```

### Provider Formatting
```rust
/// Format provider name (magenta)
pub fn format_provider_rich(provider: &str) -> String {
    format!("[magenta]{}[/]", provider)
}
```

### Timestamp Formatting
```rust
/// Format timestamp (gray, less prominent)
pub fn format_timestamp_rich(dt: &DateTime<Utc>) -> String {
