 {"id":"rust_proxy-y9o","title":"Add reload command for explicit reload without signal","description":"## Scope

Add a `reload` CLI command that sends SIGHUP to the running daemon, providing a user-friendly way to trigger config reload without manually finding the PID.

## Rationale

While `kill -HUP $(cat /path/to/pidfile)` works, it's cumbersome. A dedicated `rp reload` command is:
- More discoverable
- Easier to remember
- Consistent with other CLI commands
- Provides better feedback (success/failure messages)

## Implementation Details

### CLI Command

```rust
#[derive(Debug, Subcommand)]
enum Commands {
    // ... existing commands

    /// Reload daemon configuration without restart
    Reload,
}
```

### Implementation

```rust
fn reload_cmd() -> Result<()> {
    let pid = read_daemon_pid()?;

    #[cfg(unix)]
    {
        use nix::sys::signal::{kill, Signal};
        use nix::unistd::Pid;

        kill(Pid::from_raw(pid), Signal::SIGHUP)
            .context("Failed to send SIGHUP to daemon")?;

        println!("Reload signal sent to daemon (PID {})", pid);
        println!("Check daemon logs for reload status");
        Ok(())
    }

    #[cfg(not(unix))]
    {
        anyhow::bail!("Reload command not supported on this platform");
    }
}

fn read_daemon_pid() -> Result<i32> {
    let pid_path = pid_file_path()?;
    let content = fs::read_to_string(&pid_path)
        .with_context(|| format!("No running daemon (missing {})", pid_path.display()))?;
    content.trim().parse()
        .context("Invalid PID in pidfile")
}
```

### User Experience

```
$ rp reload
Reload signal sent to daemon (PID 12345)
Check daemon logs for reload status

$ rp reload
Error: No running daemon (missing /var/run/rp/rp.pid)

$ rp status  # Could show last reload time
Daemon: running (PID 12345)
Last config reload: 2025-01-18 10:30:00
Config file: /etc/rp/config.toml
```

### Alternative: IPC-Based Reload

For richer feedback, consider using IPC (Unix socket) instead of just signals:

```rust
// Future enhancement: daemon listens on socket for commands
// Client sends "reload" command, gets back result
```

This is more complex but enables:
- Synchronous feedback (reload succeeded/failed)
- Richer error messages
- Config diff in response

For now, signal-based is simpler and sufficient.

## Acceptance Criteria

- `rp reload` sends SIGHUP to running daemon
- Clear error message if no daemon running
- Success message with PID
- Works on Unix systems
- Graceful error on unsupported platforms","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-18T18:56:57.852651983Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-18T18:56:57.852651983Z","compaction_level":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rust_proxy-y9o","depends_on_id":"rust_proxy-3q7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-18T18:57:07.087318535Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","metadata":"","thread_id":""}]}
