 {"id":"rust_proxy-zap","title":"Implement completion script generation using clap_complete","description":"## Scope

Use clap_complete to generate shell-specific completion scripts for bash, zsh, and fish.

## Implementation Details

### Add clap_complete Dependency

```toml
[dependencies]
clap_complete = "4"
```

### Script Generation

```rust
use clap_complete::{generate, shells::{Bash, Zsh, Fish}};

pub fn generate_completions(shell: Shell) -> String {
    let mut cmd = Cli::command();
    let mut buf = Vec::new();

    match shell {
        Shell::Bash => generate(Bash, &mut cmd, "rp", &mut buf),
        Shell::Zsh => generate(Zsh, &mut cmd, "rp", &mut buf),
        Shell::Fish => generate(Fish, &mut cmd, "rp", &mut buf),
        Shell::Unknown => panic!("Cannot generate completions for unknown shell"),
    }

    String::from_utf8(buf).expect("clap_complete generates valid UTF-8")
}
```

### Testing Generation

Ensure scripts are valid by checking they contain expected content:

```rust
#[test]
fn test_bash_completions() {
    let script = generate_completions(Shell::Bash);
    assert!(script.contains("complete -F"));
    assert!(script.contains("rp"));
}

#[test]
fn test_zsh_completions() {
    let script = generate_completions(Shell::Zsh);
    assert!(script.contains("#compdef rp"));
}

#[test]
fn test_fish_completions() {
    let script = generate_completions(Shell::Fish);
    assert!(script.contains("complete -c rp"));
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- clap_complete dependency added
